verbose_text: In the reactions using K6-Ub2 and K48-Ub2, which did not bind to BRAP (124-569) in the Biacore assay (XREF_FIG), the usage of the di-ubiquitin chain (Ub2) (XREF_FIG) and signal intensities for total ubiquitylation and auto-ubiquitylated BRAP (XREF_FIG) were strikingly low, whereas the level of BRAP (124-569) remaining after the 90-min reaction remained high (XREF_FIG).
evidence: K6-Ub2 and K48-Ub2, which did not bind to BRAP
